---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>Engineering | jomcgi</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
            font-size: 14px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background: var(--bg);
            color: var(--fg);
            --bg: #fff;
            --fg: #000;
        }

        body.dark {
            --bg: #000;
            --fg: #fff;
        }

        a {
            color: var(--fg);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }

        header {
            margin-bottom: 60px;
            padding-bottom: 30px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--fg);
        }

        .header-top {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .back-link {
            font-size: 12px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            text-decoration: none;
            opacity: 0.7;
        }

        .back-link:hover {
            opacity: 1;
        }

        .toggle-btn {
            background: transparent;
            color: var(--fg);
            border: 2px solid var(--fg);
            padding: 6px 12px;
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
            font-size: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .toggle-btn:hover {
            background: var(--fg);
            color: var(--bg);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 4px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .subtitle {
            font-size: 14px;
            opacity: 0.7;
            max-width: 600px;
        }

        .deep-dive {
            margin-bottom: 80px;
            scroll-margin-top: 40px;
        }

        .deep-dive-header {
            display: flex;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--fg);
        }

        .deep-dive-number {
            font-size: 11px;
            opacity: 0.5;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 3px;
        }

        h3 {
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            margin: 30px 0 15px 0;
            padding-bottom: 8px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg);
        }

        .motivation {
            background: var(--fg);
            color: var(--bg);
            padding: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        .motivation-label {
            font-size: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            opacity: 0.7;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .motivation-text {
            font-size: 15px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .diagram-container {
            margin: 25px 0;
            padding: 30px;
            border: 2px solid var(--fg);
            background: var(--bg);
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        .mermaid {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        .mermaid svg {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
        }

        .mermaid svg .edgeLabel {
            background-color: var(--bg) !important;
        }

        .mermaid svg .edgeLabel rect {
            fill: var(--bg) !important;
            opacity: 1 !important;
        }

        .mermaid svg .cluster rect {
            stroke: #888 !important;
            stroke-dasharray: 5 5 !important;
        }

        .execution {
            margin-top: 25px;
        }

        .execution-label {
            font-size: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            opacity: 0.5;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .execution-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
            gap: 0;
            border: 2px solid var(--fg);
        }

        .execution-row {
            display: contents;
        }

        .execution-key {
            padding: 12px 15px;
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 12px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg);
            border-right: 2px solid var(--fg);
            background: var(--bg);
        }

        .execution-value {
            padding: 12px 15px;
            font-size: 13px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg);
        }

        .execution-row:last-child .execution-key,
        .execution-row:last-child .execution-value {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        pre {
            border: 2px solid var(--fg);
            padding: 15px;
            font-size: 12px;
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 20px 0;
            background: var(--bg);
        }

        code {
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
        }

        .subsection {
            margin: 40px 0;
            scroll-margin-top: 40px;
        }

        .subsection-header {
            font-size: 12px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            opacity: 0.7;
        }

        .live-link {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: 2px solid var(--fg);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 12px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }

        .live-link:hover {
            background: var(--fg);
            color: var(--bg);
        }

        footer {
            margin-top: 60px;
            padding-top: 30px;
            border-top: 2px solid var(--fg);
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .footer-links {
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .footer-links a {
            font-size: 12px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            text-decoration: none;
            opacity: 0.7;
        }

        .footer-links a:hover {
            opacity: 1;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            .execution-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }

            .execution-key {
                border-right: none;
                border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg);
                background: var(--fg);
                color: var(--bg);
            }

            .execution-row:last-child .execution-key {
                border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg);
            }

            .header-top {
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: flex-start;
                gap: 15px;
            }

            .subsection {
                padding-left: 15px;
            }
        }
    </style>
    <script is:inline>
        // Dark mode: check localStorage first, then system preference
        (function() {
            const stored = localStorage.getItem('darkMode');
            if (stored === 'true') {
                document.documentElement.classList.add('dark-pending');
            } else if (stored === 'false') {
                // Explicitly light mode
            } else if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches) {
                document.documentElement.classList.add('dark-pending');
            }
        })();
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <script is:inline>
        // Apply dark mode immediately to avoid flash
        if (document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark-pending')) {
            document.body.classList.add('dark');
            document.documentElement.classList.remove('dark-pending');
        }

        window.toggleDarkMode = function() {
            document.body.classList.toggle('dark');
            localStorage.setItem('darkMode', document.body.classList.contains('dark'));
        };
    </script>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="header-top">
                <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; jomcgi.dev</a>
                <button class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleDarkMode()">INVERT</button>
            </div>
            <h1>Engineering Notes</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Deep dives into interesting problems I've solved. Each section covers the motivation and execution.</p>
        </header>

        <!-- Deep Dive 1: Claude Code Web -->
        <section class="deep-dive" id="claude-code">
            <div class="deep-dive-header">
                <span class="deep-dive-number">01</span>
                <h2>Claude Code Web: In-Cluster AI Assistant</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="motivation">
                <div class="motivation-label">Motivation</div>
                <div class="motivation-text">
                    I wanted a coding assistant that could see what's actually happening in my cluster—read logs,
                    check pod status, query traces—without me having to copy-paste context. Running Claude Code
                    in-cluster with MCP servers gives it direct access. A local llama-cpp instance handles simpler
                    tasks without external API calls.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="diagram-container">
                <MermaidDiagram diagram={claudeCodeDiagram} id="claude-code" />
            </div>

            <div class="execution">
                <div class="execution-label">Execution</div>
                <div class="execution-grid">
                    <div class="execution-row">
                        <div class="execution-key">Local LLM</div>
                        <div class="execution-value">Hermes 4.3-36B IQ4_XS on a 4090. GGUF quantization fits in 24GB VRAM. 32k context window. Flash attention and quantized KV cache for fast inference.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="execution-row">
                        <div class="execution-key">Model Routing</div>
                        <div class="execution-value">Claude for complex reasoning and architecture decisions. Local llama-cpp for code generation, refactoring, and directed tasks.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="execution-row">
                        <div class="execution-key">SigNoz MCP</div>
                        <div class="execution-value">Direct access to logs, traces, and metrics. "Why is this pod crashlooping?" becomes answerable without leaving the conversation.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="execution-row">
                        <div class="execution-key">Cluster Context</div>
                        <div class="execution-value">Read-only Kubernetes API access. Check deployment status, resource usage, recent events. The assistant knows what's running and what's broken.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Deep Dive 2: Trips - Camera to Browser -->
        <section class="deep-dive" id="trips">
            <div class="deep-dive-header">
                <span class="deep-dive-number">02</span>
                <h2>Trips: Camera to Browser</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="motivation">
                <div class="motivation-label">Motivation</div>
                <div class="motivation-text">
                    I wanted an easy way to share trips with friends and family. A GoPro on the dash captures photos automatically,
                    and my homelab turns them into a live feed they can follow along with - or replay later. Works for anything with GPS-tagged photos.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="diagram-container">
                <MermaidDiagram diagram={tripsPipelineDiagram} id="trips" />
            </div>

            <a href="https://trips.jomcgi.dev" target="_blank" class="live-link">View Live at trips.jomcgi.dev →</a>

            <!-- Subsection A: Capture -->
            <div class="subsection">
                <div class="subsection-header">A. Capture</div>
                <p>The GoPro shoots on interval while driving. A Python controller manages the camera over WiFi, handling connection drops and queueing downloads for later.</p>

                <div class="execution">
                    <div class="execution-grid">
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Async Camera</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">Python asyncio controller. GPS-triggered capture at configurable intervals. 27MP RAW with JPG fallback when storage is tight.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">SQLite Queue</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">Persistent download queue survives restarts. Exponential backoff on WiFi drops. Resume exactly where we left off.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">EXIF Extraction</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">Camera optics preserved: ISO, aperture, shutter speed, focal length. GPS coordinates embedded. Deterministic UUIDs from content hash.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Subsection B: Event Store -->
            <div class="subsection">
                <div class="subsection-header">B. Event Store</div>
                <p>Trip points are events in NATS JetStream. The API replays the stream on startup to rebuild state. No database needed—just an append-only log.</p>

                <div class="execution">
                    <div class="execution-grid">
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Stream Replay</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">On startup, ephemeral consumer replays entire stream. Rebuilds in-memory cache from event history. ~200ms for 10k events.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Live Subscribe</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">After replay, durable consumer subscribes to new events. Cache stays current. Multiple API pods can subscribe without conflicts.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Tombstones</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">Deletions are events too. Tombstone message marks a point as deleted. Replay respects tombstones. No orphaned data.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Subsection C: Delivery -->
            <div class="subsection">
                <div class="subsection-header">C. Delivery</div>
                <p>GoPro images are 27MB each. imgproxy generates thumbnails and display sizes on-the-fly. Cloudflare CDN caches everything at the edge—most requests never hit my homelab.</p>

                <div class="execution">
                    <div class="execution-grid">
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Deterministic Keys</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">UUID v5 from namespace + content hash. Same image always gets same key. Idempotent uploads. No duplicates ever.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">imgproxy</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">On-the-fly resizing from SeaweedFS. /thumb/* → 300px, /display/* → 1920x1080. WebP/AVIF based on Accept header.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="execution-row">
                            <div class="execution-key">Cloudflare CDN</div>
                            <div class="execution-value">Immutable cache-control headers. Content-addressed keys mean cache invalidation is never needed. Edge-cached globally.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Subsection D: Display -->
